# ============================================================================
# MINIMAL TEST OBJ - For basic parsing tests
# ============================================================================
#
# PURPOSE:
#   The simplest possible valid OBJ file - a single triangle. Used to test
#   the parser's handling of minimal input without materials or normals.
#
# TESTS:
#   - Basic vertex (v) parsing
#   - Basic face (f) parsing with vertex-only format
#   - Automatic face normal generation (when no vn provided)
#   - Minimal file handling
#   - Default material assignment (index 0)
#
# EXPECTED RESULTS:
#   - Triangle count: 1
#   - Material count: 1 (default material only)
#   - Generated normal: (0, 0, 1) - perpendicular to XY plane
#   - Vertices form right triangle in XY plane
#
# GEOMETRY:
#        V2 (0.5, 1, 0)
#           /\
#          /  \
#         /    \
#   V0 (0,0,0)--V1 (1,0,0)
#
# FACE WINDING:
#   Counter-clockwise when viewed from +Z
#   Normal points in +Z direction
#
# ============================================================================

# Three vertices defining a triangle in the XY plane
v 0.0 0.0 0.0
v 1.0 0.0 0.0
v 0.5 1.0 0.0

# Single face referencing all three vertices (1-based indexing)
f 1 2 3

